&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cardio-Thoracic Scrub Practitioner Band 6&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have permanent vacancies as part of the Oxford Heart Centre expansion within our Cardio-thoracic theatres.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our work is based in our 3 Theatre suite including clinical work in the Cardiac Angiography suite.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to join a supportive cohesive team that provides an excellent standard of care for patient’s undergoing cardio-thoracic surgery and cardiac angiography, then this could be the job for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a forward thinking motivated practitioner (RN’s and ODP’s) who would like to join our expanding team of Cardio-thoracic practitioners enabling the individual to experience or consolidate their existing skills in Cardio-thoracic Surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We provide a supportive working environment for you to develop the necessary skills to fulfil this perioperative practitioner role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a structured preceptorship, mentorship and education programme. We support staff to attend our in house Peri- Operative Care Course. There are also opportunities to attend and present at national conferences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All posts involve working an on call commitment, to cover out of hour’s emergency work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date : 15th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Planned interview date : 10th December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAyrin MargalloJob titleSisterEmail addressayrin.margallo@ouh.nhs.ukTelephone number01865-857800Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sister Ayrin Margallo tel. No. 01865857800 or e mail address: ayrin.margallo@ouh.nhs.uk.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The contact person is usually available 4 days a week. If you would like to arrange an informal visit please contact the name above.&lt;/p&gt;
